// `arche run` is the dev-iteration path → defaults to device-granular INCREMENTAL codegen (per-unit +
// per-device object cache), so editing one device only recompiles that device. `arche build` stays
// whole-program. `--whole-program` opts run out. Here ARCHE_CACHE_DIR is set explicitly to keep the test
// hermetic (run otherwise anchors the cache to the project dir).
//
// run defaults to incremental → per-unit objects land in the cache, and the program runs correctly.
// RUN: rm -rf %t.cache && env ARCHE_CACHE_DIR=%t.cache %arche run %s | grep -qF "run_ok"
// RUN: ls %t.cache/*.o
// a second run still works (reusing the cached device objects).
// RUN: env ARCHE_CACHE_DIR=%t.cache %arche run %s | grep -qF "run_ok"
//
// `--whole-program` opts out → no per-unit object cache is produced, program still runs.
// RUN: rm -rf %t.cache2 && env ARCHE_CACHE_DIR=%t.cache2 %arche run --whole-program %s | grep -qF "run_ok"
// RUN: ! ls %t.cache2/*.o
#import { fmt }
main :: proc() {
  fmt.print("run_ok\n")();
}
